data.title: The Royal Watcher
data.text:
Royal and Noble Guests and Relatives gathered from around Europe to celebrate the Wedding of Duchess Katharina of Oldenburg and Count Clemens Moy de Sons in Rastede in Oldenburg on July 13th.

Continue reading →

Royal and Noble Guests and Relatives from around Europe gathered to celebrate the Wedding of Archduke Pál von Habsburg-Lothringen and Antonia Lütz at the Bonner Münster in Bonn on July 27th. Continue reading →

Today marks the 70th Anniversary of the Death of Crown Princess Antonia of Bavaria, who passed away on this day in 1954! The Luxembourg Princess who married the last Bavarian Crown Prince and was imprisoned in a Concentration Camp during the Second World War, Crown Princess Antonia possessed some splendid royal heirlooms, including the magnificent Bavarian Ruby Tiara!

Continue reading →

Happy Birthday to Princess Dorothea of Hesse, Princess of Windish-Grätz, who turns 90 today! The daughter of Prince Christoph of Hesse and Princess Sophie of Greece and Hanover who married Prince Friedrich Karl of Windisch-Grätz and is a first cousin of King Charles III, Princess Dorothea possessed some spectacular jewels, including the magnificent Hesse Aquamarine Tiara and Parure!

Continue reading →

Royal and Noble Guests and Relatives gathered to celebrate the Wedding of Princess Clarissa zu Fürstenberg and Alexander Cass Saint at the Erzabtei St. Martin Beuron in Baden-Württemberg last weekend, followed by a Reception at Schloss Werenwag.

Continue reading →

Today marks the 110th Anniversary of the Birth of Princess Sophie of Greece and Hannover, who was born on this day in 1914! The sister of the late Duke of Edinburgh, Princess Sophie was married to Prince Christoph of Hesse and after his untimely death during the Second World War, married Prince George William of Hanover, being a constant presence at Greek, British, and German Royal events throughout the 20th century, so we are featuring her heirloom Hesse Emerald Cross!

Continue reading →

Happy Birthday to Duchess Marie-Caroline in Bavaria, Duchess Philipp of Württemberg, who celebrates her 55th Birthday today! The illustrious Bavarian Duchess who married (and divorced) the prominent art expert, Duke Philipp of Württemberg, Duchess Marie-Caroline has worn several specular heirlooms, but her collection includes this spectacular modern Topaz and Diamond Suite!

Continue reading →

Royal Guests and Relatives gathered from around Europe to celebrate the Wedding of Prince Constantin von Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Glücksburg and Countess Sophia von der Schulenburg at the Església de Sant Bartolomeu in Mallorca on June 1st.

Continue reading →
